{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Compared to others, our method achieves the best overall attack success rate.",
    "Notably, it even reaches an astonishing success rate of 98.7% in the category of violence/crime.",
    "However, it slightly falls short of VAJM's performance in the x-risk category.",
    "This discrepancy is because the majority of harmful instructions in the x-risk category are formulated as questions, which differ from the declarative or directive formats used in the optimization samples for our adversarial attacks.To further broaden our evaluation, we utilize the challenging subset of RealToxicityPrompts benchmark [10], which includes 1,225 text prompts designed to trigger toxic continuations.",
    "Given that this is a text continuation task, we exclude the GCG method [30], which focuses on generating text suffixes, from our comparison."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This discrepancy is because the majority of harmful instructions in the x-risk category are formulated as questions, which differ from the declarative or directive formats used in the optimization samples for our adversarial attacks.To further broaden our evaluation, we utilize the challenging subset of RealToxicityPrompts benchmark [10], which includes 1,225 text prompts designed to trigger toxic continuations.",
    "Given that this is a text continuation task, we exclude the GCG method [30], which focuses on generating text suffixes, from our comparison."
